[{"text": "Jupiter may be the biggest planet ", "start": 6.239, "duration": 2.936}, {"text": "in the Solar System,", "start": 9.175, "duration": 1.268}, {"text": "but its days are numbered.", "start": 10.443, "duration": 3.203}, {"text": "Because today, we\u2019re using Earth\u2019s biggest,", "start": 13.646, "duration": 3.604}, {"text": "baddest bombs", "start": 17.25, "duration": 1.502}, {"text": "to blow the gas giant", "start": 18.752, "duration": 1.768}, {"text": "into oblivion.", "start": 20.52, "duration": 2.803}, {"text": "Nuclear weapons are so powerful", "start": 46.112, "duration": 3.137}, {"text": "that even the low-yield versions,", "start": 49.249, "duration": 2.335}, {"text": "like those dropped on Japan", "start": 51.584, "duration": 1.802}, {"text": "by the U.S. in World War II,", "start": 53.386, "duration": 2.236}, {"text": "have the explosive equivalent", "start": 55.622, "duration": 2.469}, {"text": "of 15-20 kilotons of dynamite each.", "start": 58.091, "duration": 4.972}, {"text": "What makes them so volatile", "start": 63.063, "duration": 1.901}, {"text": "is that they harness", "start": 64.964, "duration": 1.235}, {"text": "the intense energy-releasing power", "start": 66.199, "duration": 2.502}, {"text": "of nuclear fission or fusion.", "start": 68.701, "duration": 3.437}, {"text": "These are the same processes", "start": 72.138, "duration": 1.902}, {"text": "that happen in our very own Sun.", "start": 74.04, "duration": 2.803}, {"text": "So be careful when moving", "start": 76.843, "duration": 1.802}, {"text": "these things out to Jupiter.", "start": 78.645, "duration": 2.035}, {"text": "One false move", "start": 80.68, "duration": 1.335}, {"text": "and you could be incinerated", "start": 82.015, "duration": 2.169}, {"text": "by a fireball as hot", "start": 84.184, "duration": 2.002}, {"text": "as the center of the Sun.", "start": 86.186, "duration": 4.104}, {"text": "In order to blow Jupiter to bits,", "start": 90.29, "duration": 3.203}, {"text": "one single bomb", "start": 93.493, "duration": 1.234}, {"text": "wouldn\u2019t necessarily be up for the task.", "start": 94.727, "duration": 2.97}, {"text": "Good thing for this scenario that", "start": 97.697, "duration": 1.835}, {"text": "there are a lot of nuclear weapons", "start": 99.532, "duration": 2.436}, {"text": "on Earth.", "start": 101.968, "duration": 1.268}, {"text": "Maybe the safest plan would be", "start": 103.236, "duration": 1.835}, {"text": "getting them all off our planet anyway.", "start": 105.071, "duration": 3.404}, {"text": "Given the top-secret nature", "start": 108.475, "duration": 2.102}, {"text": "of military activities, ", "start": 110.577, "duration": 1.401}, {"text": "it\u2019s hard to know the exact number.", "start": 111.978, "duration": 3.237}, {"text": "But estimates put the global arsenal", "start": 115.215, "duration": 2.669}, {"text": "at about 12,700,", "start": 117.884, "duration": 2.903}, {"text": "with the U.S. and Russia", "start": 120.787, "duration": 2.336}, {"text": "battling for top spot", "start": 123.123, "duration": 1.735}, {"text": "with 5,500 to 6,000 weapons each.", "start": 124.858, "duration": 4.804}, {"text": "OK, there\u2019s no use in delaying.", "start": 129.662, "duration": 2.136}, {"text": "Let\u2019s get these rockets off Earth", "start": 131.798, "duration": 1.735}, {"text": "as fast as possible.", "start": 133.533, "duration": 2.636}, {"text": "The distance between Earth", "start": 136.169, "duration": 1.768}, {"text": "and Jupiter fluctuates", "start": 137.937, "duration": 1.802}, {"text": "from about 590 million km (365 million mi)", "start": 139.739, "duration": 2.169}, {"text": "to 970 million km (600,000 mi).", "start": 141.908, "duration": 3.437}, {"text": "In the past,", "start": 145.345, "duration": 1.034}, {"text": "missions like the Galileo space probe", "start": 146.379, "duration": 2.669}, {"text": "took nearly five years to make the journey", "start": 149.048, "duration": 2.77}, {"text": "to the gas giant.", "start": 151.818, "duration": 1.668}, {"text": "But our rockets wouldn\u2019t take this long.", "start": 153.486, "duration": 3.737}, {"text": "Galileo had to be slow enough", "start": 157.223, "duration": 1.835}, {"text": "to enter Jupiter\u2019s orbit.", "start": 159.058, "duration": 1.635}, {"text": "We\u2019d just need to hit the planet head-on.", "start": 160.693, "duration": 2.203}, {"text": "So you\u2019d only be looking", "start": 162.896, "duration": 1.668}, {"text": "at about 550 ", "start": 164.564, "duration": 1.868}, {"text": "to 650 days to get the job done.", "start": 166.432, "duration": 3.437}, {"text": "You shouldn\u2019t be too reckless", "start": 169.869, "duration": 2.002}, {"text": "and speedy, though.", "start": 171.871, "duration": 1.068}, {"text": "You don\u2019t want to nuke something else", "start": 172.939, "duration": 1.902}, {"text": "by accident.", "start": 174.841, "duration": 1.335}, {"text": "Bypassing the Moon", "start": 176.176, "duration": 1.768}, {"text": "and Mars would be easy enough,", "start": 177.944, "duration": 1.702}, {"text": "but getting safely through the asteroid belt", "start": 179.646, "duration": 2.936}, {"text": "would be like navigating a minefield.", "start": 182.582, "duration": 3.236}, {"text": "There are millions of asteroids", "start": 185.818, "duration": 2.236}, {"text": "riddled between Mars and Jupiter.", "start": 188.054, "duration": 1.969}, {"text": "And while the average distance \nbetween them", "start": 190.023, "duration": 2.736}, {"text": "is a not-so-worrisome", "start": 192.759, "duration": 2.035}, {"text": "966,000 km (600,000 mi),", "start": 194.794, "duration": 2.403}, {"text": "sometimes it can still get", "start": 197.197, "duration": 2.235}, {"text": "a little cramped in there.", "start": 199.432, "duration": 1.468}, {"text": "And Jupiter is partly to blame for this.", "start": 200.9, "duration": 3.537}, {"text": "The planet\u2019s massive", "start": 204.437, "duration": 1.502}, {"text": "gravitational influence", "start": 205.939, "duration": 1.601}, {"text": "causes many of these", "start": 207.54, "duration": 1.301}, {"text": "to group into clusters", "start": 208.841, "duration": 1.502}, {"text": "known as families.", "start": 210.343, "duration": 1.735}, {"text": "Carelessly navigate through one,", "start": 212.078, "duration": 2.169}, {"text": "like the Flora family,", "start": 214.247, "duration": 1.768}, {"text": "and you\u2019d better hope none of our rockets", "start": 216.015, "duration": 2.503}, {"text": "would collide with any of its 400 asteroids.", "start": 218.518, "duration": 4.071}, {"text": "For the best chance of success,", "start": 222.589, "duration": 2.469}, {"text": "you should aim to transport your rockets", "start": 225.058, "duration": 2.068}, {"text": "through the Kirkwood gaps.", "start": 227.126, "duration": 1.869}, {"text": "These are nearly asteroid-free", "start": 228.995, "duration": 2.569}, {"text": "regions in the belt.", "start": 231.564, "duration": 1.402}, {"text": "Because you\u2019d hate to see", "start": 232.966, "duration": 1.701}, {"text": "all of our planet\u2019s nukes", "start": 234.667, "duration": 1.335}, {"text": "detonate themselves", "start": 236.002, "duration": 1.168}, {"text": "in a blinding chain reaction", "start": 237.17, "duration": 1.868}, {"text": "before reaching our target.", "start": 239.038, "duration": 2.57}, {"text": "As the first of our bombs", "start": 241.608, "duration": 1.935}, {"text": "exploded on Jupiter,", "start": 243.543, "duration": 1.535}, {"text": "you\u2019d see bright flashes", "start": 245.078, "duration": 1.968}, {"text": "back here on Earth.", "start": 247.046, "duration": 1.435}, {"text": "Just like when the \nShoemaker-Levy 9 comet", "start": 248.481, "duration": 2.97}, {"text": "slammed into Jupiter in 1994.", "start": 251.451, "duration": 2.769}, {"text": "But that only released 5% as much energy", "start": 254.22, "duration": 3.971}, {"text": "as the Tsar Bomba,", "start": 258.191, "duration": 1.735}, {"text": "the largest bomb ever created.", "start": 259.926, "duration": 3.036}, {"text": "So with thousands of our nuclear bombs,", "start": 262.962, "duration": 3.37}, {"text": "Jupiter\u2019s days would have to be numbered,", "start": 266.332, "duration": 2.036}, {"text": "right?", "start": 268.368, "duration": 1.067}, {"text": "Well, not exactly.", "start": 269.435, "duration": 2.236}, {"text": "Even though our nukes", "start": 271.671, "duration": 1.969}, {"text": "could produce an explosion", "start": 273.64, "duration": 1.534}, {"text": "hotter than the Sun,", "start": 275.174, "duration": 1.602}, {"text": "this wouldn\u2019t cause", "start": 276.776, "duration": 1.468}, {"text": "all the hydrogen on Jupiter to ignite.", "start": 278.244, "duration": 2.669}, {"text": "It just isn\u2019t dense enough", "start": 280.913, "duration": 1.769}, {"text": "to sustain nuclear fusion.", "start": 282.682, "duration": 3.003}, {"text": "And even if every bomb was detonated,", "start": 285.685, "duration": 3.437}, {"text": " Jupiter wouldn\u2019t blow up", "start": 289.122, "duration": 1.601}, {"text": "completely either.", "start": 290.723, "duration": 1.602}, {"text": "In order to do that,", "start": 292.325, "duration": 1.668}, {"text": "we\u2019d need to unleash", "start": 293.993, "duration": 1.235}, {"text": "as much energy as the Sun releases", "start": 295.228, "duration": 2.736}, {"text": "over 160 years,", "start": 297.964, "duration": 2.869}, {"text": "all at once.", "start": 300.833, "duration": 1.702}, {"text": "And for that highly energetic result,", "start": 302.535, "duration": 3.537}, {"text": "about one billion billion nukes", "start": 306.072, "duration": 3.036}, {"text": "would be required.", "start": 309.108, "duration": 1.502}, {"text": "Somewhat more", "start": 310.61, "duration": 1.068}, {"text": "than the 12,700 in our arsenal.", "start": 311.678, "duration": 3.67}, {"text": "To build that many bombs,", "start": 315.348, "duration": 2.235}, {"text": "you\u2019d need a combined mass of material", "start": 317.583, "duration": 2.436}, {"text": "that would almost be twice that", "start": 320.019, "duration": 2.136}, {"text": "of the largest moon in the Solar System,", "start": 322.155, "duration": 2.435}, {"text": "Jupiter\u2019s Ganymede.", "start": 324.59, "duration": 2.236}, {"text": "No small feat,", "start": 326.826, "duration": 1.668}, {"text": "since it\u2019s bigger than Pluto and Mercury.", "start": 328.494, "duration": 5.272}, {"text": "All right, well,", "start": 333.766, "duration": 0.834}, {"text": "that was pretty anticlimactic.", "start": 334.6, "duration": 2.603}, {"text": "Maybe you\u2019d be better off seeing", "start": 337.203, "duration": 1.935}, {"text": "what could happen", "start": 339.138, "duration": 0.601}, {"text": "by taking things to the extreme", "start": 339.739, "duration": 1.969}, {"text": "here on Earth.", "start": 341.708, "duration": 1.601}, {"text": "Like dropping a nuke", "start": 343.309, "duration": 1.602}, {"text": "into the deepest part of the ocean.", "start": 344.911, "duration": 2.736}, {"text": "But that\u2019s a story for another WHAT IF.", "start": 347.647, "duration": 6.74}]